## Flow Spec (JSON-ish)

type Locator = { by:'css'|'role'|'testid', selector:string, hasText?:string };
type Step =
 | { type:'goto', url:string }
 | { type:'waitFor', locator:Locator, timeout?:number, description?:string }
 | { type:'click', locator:Locator, description?:string }
 | { type:'fill', locator:Locator, value:string, description?:string }
 | { type:'custom', description:string, data:{ action:string, [k:string]:any } };

interface FlowDoc { name:string; steps: Step[]; }

## Engine Rules

Background owns the state machine; content performs DOM actions and returns StepResult.

Custom actions like your navigateToFirstResult must emit a post-navigation hint { postNavigate:true, routePattern:/contacts\/\d+/ } so background arms the “phased wait” automatically.

The engine retries idempotent waits up to 2 times; mutating steps (click/fill) retry only on transient errors (detached/obscured) and never if a side effect already happened.

